CatDescriptText: Cutline for image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1959, pg. B4, reads: "Trick or Treat! - Joining the hobgoblins, witches, ghosts and other supernatural creatures on Halloween visits to homes was this 'mummy' who escaped from King Tut's tomb in Egypt. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Child wearing saddle shoes and Halloween mummy costume trick or treating at Charles "Teenie" Harris' house, 7604 Mulford Street, Homewood
